  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Enlightenment and genocide, contradictions of modernity (its publication year) is an open access scholarly book from P.I.E. Peter Lang S.A. that has become a recognised reference point in ongoing research. Its availability across open platforms positions it for growing use in both research and teaching.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Enlightenment and genocide, contradictions of modernity, published by P.I.E. Peter Lang S.A. in its publication year, is a scholarly book that contributes to ongoing discussions in its field. As part of a broader move towards more accessible and connected research, it has the potential to reach readers well beyond the boundaries of a single institution or paywalled platform.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\"> It has so far been cited 50 times in the scholarly literature, indicating that it has found a role as a reference point in ongoing research. Metadata and citation links connect the book to areas such as Genocide, Enlightenment and Europe, politics and government, 1989-, helping to position it within the wider research landscape. Taken together, these signals begin to map how the book is being taken up, cited, and positioned within current academic debates.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\"> No public web mentions have been detected through Crossref Event Data, which is still common for many academic books and does not diminish its potential relevance. Public usage statistics from open-access infrastructure are not yet available or not exposed for this title, so much of its readership remains invisible in the data. As more readers discover the work and as additional platforms index and surface it, its influence can continue to grow \u2013 both in formal scholarship and in how researchers, students, and practitioners engage with its ideas in the future.</p>",
